description:
&lt;p&gt;The following post has become available within KMPT for a dynamic, self-motivated,&lt;br /&gt;forward thinking administrator. The post will be within the Liaison Psychiatry Team (this&lt;br /&gt;service provides mental health assessments for patients presenting or currently staying&lt;br /&gt;within hospital) for 22.5 hours per week. 3 x weekday evenings 15:30-20:30 and 1 x&lt;br /&gt;weekend 9:00-17:00 after initial induction. The post holder will be required to cover day&lt;br /&gt;shifts to cover absence as and when required. The post will be based at Medway&lt;br /&gt;hospital although the successful candidate may be required on occasion to provide&lt;br /&gt;support to the other North Kent Hospital sites. This role does not involve patient&lt;br /&gt;contact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be educated to GCSE grade C in Maths and English or equivalent.&lt;br /&gt;Possess 5 GCSE grade A-C. NVQ Level 2/3 or equivalent in Administration and have a&lt;br /&gt;minimum 2 years experience of working within an administration role. Applications that&lt;br /&gt;do not meet these requirements may not be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have excellent organisational and analytical skills, be&lt;br /&gt;competent in data entry, possess a good working knowledge of Microsoft Office&lt;br /&gt;packages such as Excel, pay attention to detail, and be a good team player. They&lt;br /&gt;should be able to work unsupervised, meet tight deadlines and adapt to&lt;br /&gt;changing/challenging situations. As part of the interview process candidates will be&lt;br /&gt;required to undertake literacy, numeracy and other relevant assessments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To deliver an effective service it is essential that you are able to travel between&lt;br /&gt;bases in a timely manner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nicola Little, Administration Co-ordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: nicola.little1@nhs.net, Telephone: 07500573418&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Not contactable on Fridays)&lt;/p&gt;
